&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**THIS VACANCY IS ONLY OPEN TO EMPLOYEES OF WORCESTERSHIRE ACUTE HOSPITALS NHS TRUST**&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Clinical Audit Support Officer to join Clinical Audit Team based at Worcestershire Royal Hospital. We are seeking an enthusiastic and motivated individual who will contribute to the delivery of the Trust’s Quality Improvement Strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key duties include;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide administrative support to the Clinical Audit Team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and design audit tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce basic analysis for audit projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor active audit projects, including the quality of the information input to the Clinical Audit Tracking System.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the preparation and organisation of training and events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide advice to clinicians and other staff on the audit process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compile data for reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with the general administration of National Confidential Enquiries into Patient Outcomes &amp; Death and National Audit Projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For informal enquires please contact Jo Howden, Clinical Audit Manager on 01905 763333. EXT 38632 or email jo.howden@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
